### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3002/api/health

###

### ----------------------------------------------------
### PROJECTS API TESTS
### ----------------------------------------------------

### 1. Create a Project
# NOTE: You MUST replace `YOUR_USER_ID_HERE` with the actual User ID 
# you create in Prisma Studio (see instructions).
POST http://localhost:3002/api/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Second Project",
  "description": "Second Project!",
  "userId": "9f58550a-87e0-462e-8aca-f983b26c569b"
}

###

### 2. Get All Projects
GET http://localhost:3002/api/projects

###

### 3. Update a Project (Replace YOUR_PROJECT_ID_HERE)
PATCH http://localhost:3002/api/projects/35c4ae9d-1cba-462d-8fe9-3deb5906a4a5
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "I updated this description via PATCH"
}

###

### 4. Delete a Project (Replace YOUR_PROJECT_ID_HERE)
DELETE http://localhost:3002/api/projects/35c4ae9d-1cba-462d-8fe9-3deb5906a4a5

### ----------------------------------------------------
### IMPORTS API TESTS
### ----------------------------------------------------

### 1. Create an Import Job
# Replace YOUR_PROJECT_ID_HERE with an ID from the 'Get All Projects' response
POST http://localhost:3002/api/imports
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "projectId": "db4ab67d-d4a5-4322-8640-5a899efc8a22",
  "fileName": "test.csv",
  "filePath": "/uploads/test.csv"
}

###

### 2. Get All Imports 
GET http://localhost:3002/api/imports

###

### 3. Get Imports by Project ID
GET http://localhost:3002/api/imports?projectId=a92d58ba-24cb-4062-848a-446252077c2b

###

### 4. Update Import Status (Replace YOUR_IMPORT_ID_HERE)
PATCH http://localhost:3002/api/imports/1da3e20d-abce-45a6-a062-7945fc34dabf/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "PROCESSING"
}

###

### 5. Delete an Import Job
DELETE http://localhost:3002/api/imports/1da3e20d-abce-45a6-a062-7945fc34dabf

###

### 6. Upload an Import File (Example)
# IMPORTANT: File uploads through REST Client often look like this visually.
# You need a real file named "test.csv" in the root directory to test via CLI, 
# or you can test this endpoint natively in Postman which supports file picking.
POST http://localhost:3002/api/imports/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="projectId"

a92d58ba-24cb-4062-848a-446252077c2b
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

name,email,age
Alice,alice@example.com,20
Bob,bob@example.com,30
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 7. Parse Uploaded File
# Replace YOUR_IMPORT_ID_HERE with the ID returned from the Upload endpoint
POST http://localhost:3002/api/imports/7db4d6eb-8c65-48f7-abc1-d5daf8984233/parse
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 8. Detect Schema For File Upload
# Run this AFTER you have successfully executed block #7 (Parse Uploaded File).
# Replace YOUR_IMPORT_ID_HERE with that exact same ID.
POST http://localhost:3002/api/imports/YOUR_IMPORT_ID_HERE/detect-schema
Content-Type: application/json
